article.description: The little team from the Big Apple was every bit as good as promised against the Gators.
article.headline: Florida exits early again
article.linkText: Flores over Florida: Guard leads Jaspers in win

inlines.body:
Dick Vitale's Tourney Take
Manhattan coach Bobby Gonzalez's star keeps getting brighter and brighter. His Jaspers put Florida through a buzz saw. Five city kids put on an unbelievable show. Forwards Dave Holmes and Peter Mulligan gave a brilliant performance on the interior as they combined for 29 points. Not to be left out was the incredible play of guard Luis Flores. The former Rutgers transfer put up 26 points to help end the Gators' season. So Florida's season is over, and it's obvious that coach Billy Donovan needs to get his Big Three -- sophomore guards Anthony Roberson and Matt Walsh and junior forward David Lee -- some more help.
More on Thursday's Games

article.story: GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- David Lee scored 26 points and Matt Walsh added 19 as Florida beat Eckerd 90-70 in an exhibition game Tuesday night. The Gators led by five points at halftime against the Division II Tritons, but used a 25-12 run midway through the second half to pull away. Florida, which opens the season Nov. 19 at Jacksonville, won both its exhibition games. The Gators beat Florida Southern 105-65 last week. Steve Berg led Eckerd with 22 points.
